SIMPLE: longitudinal
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Longitudinal
<hw>Lon`gi*tu"di*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>longitudinal</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to
longitude or length; <as>as, <ex>longitudinal</ex>
distance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Extending in length; in the direction of the length;
running lengthwise, as distinguished from <contr>transverse</contr>;
<as>as, the <ex>longitudinal</ex> diameter of a body</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Cheyne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Longitudinal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Longitudinal
<hw>Lon`gi*tu"di*nal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A railway sleeper lying
parallel with the rail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Longitudinally</ent>⟦br⟧
